In this letter, President Barack Obama designates all funding for Overseas Contingency Operations/Global War on Terrorism as specified by Congress in the Consolidated Appropriations Act, 2012. This designation is in accordance with section 5 of the Act and section 251(b)(2)(A) of the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act of 1985. The President includes a list of accounts outlining the specific details of this action, which are further explained in a letter from the Director of the Office of Management and Budget.